                                            <div class="dima-tabs  tabs_style_1 tabs_on_top ">
                                                <ul class="dima-tab-nav top">
                                                    <li class="tab active"><a href="#tab-1" data-toggle="tab"
                                                            aria-expanded="true"><i
                                                                class="fas fa-music"></i>Achievements</a></li>
                                                    <li id="112" class="tab"><a href="#tab-2" data-toggle="tab"
                                                            aria-expanded="false"><i
                                                                class="fas fa-star"></i>Glenn's Life</a></li>
                                                </ul>
                                                <div class="dima-tab-content">
                                                    <div id="tab-1"
                                                        class="tab-pane fade clearfix dima-tab_content active in">
                                                        <p></p>
                                                        <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ffffff;">Gajah Mada Record was founded in 1986, led by Sugama Trisnadi with its first artist Ida Laila. As time goes by, this company which operates in music labels and recordings also houses various artists such as Nia Daniaty, Obbie Messakh, Meggy Z, Caca Handika, Rama Aiphama, Puput Melati, Melisa Trisnadi (Brother of the Meatball Maker), Lenong Rumpi, Camelia Malik and others . During its existence, Gajah Mada Record has received 11 HDX Awards & 2 BASF Awards, which were prestigious awards at that time.</span></p>
                                                        <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ffffff;">In 1998, Gajah Mada Record evolved into Kampung Artis Group, which at that time focused on renting equipment and shooting locations for well-known domestic soap operas, such as Street Children, Cinta Fitri, Tendangan si Madun, Sahaya Cinta, Taj Mahal, Islam KTP , Sampeyan Musilm and others. In 2008, Kampung Artis Group received a Muri record award as the largest shooting location.</span></p>
                                                        <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ffffff;">In the 90s, Gajah Mada Record was also a pioneer of children's songs, releasing legendary children's songs such as, "Semut-Semut Kecil, Abang Tukang Bakso, Satu Plus Satu, Si Komo, which were popularized by Melisa Trisnadi who was son of the founder of Gajah Mada Record..</span></p>
                                                        <p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ffffff;">Running until now, in 2020, Gajah Mada Record is back with new colors and concepts. Ready to contribute directly to the world of music by supporting young and talented domestic musicians. Like the twins Rizki Ridho, Indonesian Idol 2021 graduates Axl Ramanda, DRIVE, Ray Surajaya, Valdy Nyonk, Zinidin Zidan, Devta Pramesthi, Syahrul Hikmal, Ukeba Squad, Aditya Lukman, and others.</span></p>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div id="tab-2"
                                                        class="tab-pane fade clearfix dima-tab_content fade">
                                                        <p></p>
                                                        <ul>
                                                            <li><span style="color: #ffffff;">AMI Awards For
                                                                    Best Urban Production Work â Kasih Putih
                                                                    (2001)</span></li>
                                                            <li><span style="color: #ffffff;">AMI Awards For RnB
                                                                    Male Solo â Kasih Putih (2001)</span></li>
                                                            <li><span style="color: #ffffff;">AMI Awards For Pop
